    <text id="F8561T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>W. H. Buehler requests that Edward McPherson be a groomsman in his wedding, but
                    states that he understands if McPherson cannot afford the time due to matters in
                    Washington.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Edward">E</abbr> McPherson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-04-09">April 9/60</date>
                        <name type="place">Gettysburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear friend--</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I am very sorry I did not have an opportunity of seeing you when in <abbr
                        expan="Gettysburg">G</abbr>. I wanted to talk to you about several matters,
                    but was compelled to <unclear>leave</unclear>. <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> this is a very
                        <unclear>-ful</unclear> matter. I am severely thinking of getting married!
                    Foolish, you think. Go and do likewise and you will be wise, some of your
                    friends would say. Ned, if it be possible, I would like you to give me a helping
                    hand in that occasion -- the last day of <hi rend="underline">May</hi>. I want
                    John Morris and yourself. It will occupy but little of your time. You can reach
                    York by leave <pb n="2"/>
                    <abbr expan="Washington">W</abbr> at noon, and can return next day if necessary.
                        <hi rend="underline">Alice Bayler and Mary Watson</hi> will be the
                    bridesmaids. I know there might be <unclear>contingencies</unclear> in which it
                    will be difficult to <del hand="h1">not</del> leave, but if it be possible I
                    would like very much to have you present The ceremony will take place in <hi
                        rend="underline">the church</hi>.</p>

                <p>Please write me in response to it, and if you have time let me have a little
                    political consolation in matters and <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> in the <hi
                        rend="underline">East</hi>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend</salute>
                    <signed>WH Buehler</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
